## Unverified Items

Unverified opportunities and dependencies from CROSS-REQ-01 and CROSS-REQ-02 remain unpromoted. They are not official opportunities, dependencies, ownership assignments or readiness commitments until source documentation is created.

## Boundary Statement

This gap register documents blockers and next actions only. It does not authorize implementation, integration, production publication, governance execution, treasury movement, wallet signing, trading, DEX execution, marketplace settlement, mining payouts, lottery payouts, ACS provisioning, billing execution, production credentials or on-chain writes.

## 2026-06-22 - ACS-FOLLOWUP-01 Readiness Note

`READINESS_READY_LOCAL_SCOPE` means ACS has completed its local/config-first/read-only evidence chain with passing validation, completed security review and completed boundary-enforcement tests. It supports `PROMOTE_TO_L4_READINESS` only.

The ACS execution-authority opportunity and dependency chain remain blocked. Marketplace remains `HOLD` / `BACKLOG_READY` and non-executive where referenced.

## 2026-06-23 - ACS-GOV-01 Adoption Note

ACS governance adoption is `L4_READINESS_ADOPTED`. Current L-Level is `L4_READINESS`; previous L-Level was `L4_CANDIDATE`; D-Level remains `D3+`.

The remaining `GOVERNANCE_GAP` and `EXECUTION_BOUNDARY_GAP` classifications apply to execution and production authority, not to the adopted readiness maturity state. L4 Consolidated remains `NO`.

## 2026-06-23 - ACS-GOV-02 Consolidated Gate Gaps

Current L4 Consolidated assessment gaps:

- assessment-time evidence freshness
- explicit assessment authorization
- security-control disposition, threat model and incident-response notes
- cross-nucleus consistency review
- historical global snapshot reconciliation/classification
- four-role governance sign-off

These gaps do not change adopted `L4_READINESS`. They block only a future consolidated assessment. All execution and production gaps remain blocked boundaries.
